# TrackerGo / Microsoft SSO credentials
# Used by Claude to auto-fill the login form when the browser session expires.
# MFA (Microsoft Authenticator push) still requires manual approval — see note below.
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your real values:
#   cp .env.example .env
# .env is gitignored — never commit it.

TRACKERGO_EMAIL=your-email@joblogic.com
TRACKERGO_PASSWORD=your-password

# === Note on 2FA automation ===
#
# We tried to fully automate 2FA using a TOTP secret (Google Authenticator-style
# rotating 6-digit codes) so Claude could log in unattended. It is NOT possible
# in this org because the Microsoft Entra "Authentication Methods" policy only
# permits Microsoft Authenticator (push notifications). Adding a third-party
# software OATH token / "different authenticator app" is blocked at the tenant
# level, and the option does not appear in
# https://mysignins.microsoft.com/security-info.
#
# In practice this is not a big deal:
#   - The browser session in browser-data/ lasts ~8 hours after you click
#     "Yes" on "Stay signed in?", so MFA only happens once per workday.
#   - When MFA is needed, Claude will auto-fill email + password and just ask
#     you to approve the push notification on your phone (~5 seconds).
